<module>
    <h>bocsa</h>
    <p><g>bocsa</g>
        <en>a box</en> is a masculine <a href="?xx=nouns/simple_common_nouns">simple common
        noun</a>.</p>

    <p>Examples of <g>bocsa</g> as the subject of the predicative verb <a href="?gd=bi"
            ><g>bi</g></a> – <ul>
            <!--<li>indefinite – <xl>
            </xl>
            </li>-->
            <li>pre-specified – <ul>
                    <li>definite article – <g>am bocsa</g>
                        <en>the box</en> – <ul>
                            <li>unmodified – <xl>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>Càit a bheil am bocsa? Tha am bocsa air a’ bhòrd.</gd>
                                        <tr>Where is the box? The box is on the table.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                                    </li>
                                </xl>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>
    <!--<p>Examples of <g>bocsa</g> as the subject of other verbs – <ul>
            <li>indefinite –</li>
            <li>definite –</li>
        </ul>
    </p>
    -->
    <p>Examples of <g>bocsa</g> as the object of a (transitive) verb – <ul>
            <!--<li>indefinite –</li>-->
            <li>pre-specified – <ul>
                    <li>definite article – <g>am bocsa</g>
                        <en>the box</en> – <ul>
                            <li>unmodified – <xl>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>Có chuir am bocsa air a’ bhòrd? Chuir Màiri.</gd>
                                        <tr>Who put the box on the table? Mary did.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                                    </li>
                                </xl>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>

    <p>Examples of <g>bocsa</g> as the complement of the preposition <a href="?gd=an^preposition"
                ><g>an</g></a>
        <en>in</en> – <ul>
            <!--<li>indefinite –</li>-->
            <li>pre-specified – <ul>
                    <li>definite article – <g>anns a’ bhocsa</g>
                        <en>in the box</en> – <ul>
                            <li>unmodified – <xl>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>Dé tha anns a’ bhocsa sin? Tha uighean anns a’
                                            bhocsa.</gd>
                                        <tr>What is in that box? There are eggs in the box.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>Nach robh leabhar anns a’ bhocsa sin? Bha.</gd>
                                        <tr>Wasn’t there a book in that box? Yes, there was.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                                    </li>
                                </xl>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>








